  "type": "spell",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Drawing on the deepest fears of a group of creatures, you create illusory creatures in their minds, visible only to them. Each creature of your choice in a 30-foot-radius sphere centered on a point of your choice within range must make a Wisdom saving throw. On a failed save, a creature becomes <em>frightened</em> and <em>paralyzed</em> with fear for the duration. The illusion calls on the creature's deepest fears, manifesting its worst nightmares as an implacable threat. At the end of each of the <em>paralyzed</em> creature's turns, it must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or take [[/r 5d10]] psychic damage. On a successful save, the creature are no longer <em>paralyzed</em> (but still <em>frightened</em>).</p>",
